## EXISTING FACTS (already in the graph — do not duplicate)

{% if existing_facts is defined and existing_facts %}
| Subject | Predicate | Object |
|---------|-----------|--------|
{% for f in existing_facts %}
| {{ f.subject }} | {{ f.predicate }} | {{ f.object }} |
{% endfor %}

**Deduplication rule:** The graph can only have one edge between the same
pair of nodes with the same relationship type.  If a fact already exists,
do not add another.  Check not just exact matches but also synonym
predicates (works_at ≈ employed_by, studied_at ≈ attended, likes ≈ enjoys,
colleague_of ≈ coworker_of, friend_of ≈ shares_friend_with, etc.) —
these are the same edge with different words.
{% endif %}

